Reverse Each Word in a String | Reverse each word in a sentence while keeping their order. |


class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "The quick brown fox jumps";
        System.out.println("Reverse String: "+ reverseString(str));
    }
    public static String reverseString(String str){
        String[] words = str.split("\\s+");
        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        for(String word : words){
            StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder(word);
            result.append(s.reverse().toString()).append(" ");
        }
        return result.toString().trim();
    }
}

output:
Reverse String: ehT kciuq nworb xof spmuj

Explanation:
Uses split("\\s+") â€“ handles multiple spaces between words.
Uses StringBuilder to reverse each word.
Appends a space after each reversed word.
Uses trim() to remove the trailing space.
